@NODE "1.0" "1.0"

 1.0            No information.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "2.0" "2.0"

 2.0              First version I owned.
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° Only works on kickstart 2.x (Sometimes)
                ° Written by Steve Tibbett.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "3.0" "3.0"

 3.0   28-Sep-94  Released only to ßeta testers
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° I (Dave Jones) took over.
                ° Some obvious optimisations were made.
                ° Now works on WorkBench 3, as I now patch the
                  Intuition/SetWindowPointerA() function as well as the
                  Intuition/SetPointer() function.
                ° Added auto-detatch code, no more need to `RUN PointerX'.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "3.01" "3.01"

 3.01  23-Oct-94  First Full Public Release - Appeared on AUI coverdisk
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° Fixed NewSetWindowPointer().
                  It no longer causes Enforcer hits.
                ° If you now run PointerX twice, it'll Uninstall itself.
                ° Uses FastMem if available.
                ° Improved auto-detatch code.
                ° Various small optimisations.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "3.02" "3.02"

 3.02 27-Oct-94   Not publically released. Released only to Beta testers
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° More PC relativity added.
                ° Some obscure optimisations added.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "3.03" "3.03"

 3.03 7-Nov-94    Not released : personal test version
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° Code is now 100% PC Relative.
                ° Code has had loads of optimisations made, both for speed
                  and size, and is now as small and fast as possible.
                ° Fixed a harmless bug in the auto-detatch code.
                ° Removed some redundant code.
                ° Finally removed some spelling mistakes in this doc!
                  previous versions stated I was 21, Hmm.. too much Vodka..
                  (or maybe not enough ;-)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "3.04" "3.04"

 3.04 8-Nov-94    Second public release.
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° Removed an enforcer hit that's been there since ?????
                  My serial lead was broken, so my terminal wasn't getting
                  the enforcer hit messages! Sorry!
                ° Some more small optimisations, removal of duplicate code.
                ° Now uses minimal amount of CPU time even when in the
                  `busy' state. - Virtually nil when not `busy'.
                ° Corrected several mistakes in the docs, which referenced
                  MoveVBR (One of my other programs) that's what you get
                  for being lazy, and modifying another doc. ;-)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "3.05" "3.05"

 3.05 26-Dec-94   Third public release - Uploaded to AmiNet.
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° Uses an optimised SegSplit routine, 4 bytes saved! ;^)
                ° Now includes a rather nice icon.
                ° More spell checking done on docs ;-Ţ
                ° Funky new icon by Kirem Rahmani. [Spe3Kdr@Cardiff.ac.uk]

                This version seems to be the most spread version of all.
                Aminet rules! It has also appeared on the Amiga Shopper
                Subscribers disk, which Future Publishing kindly sent me
                a copy of. This is more like it! Take note AUI!
@ENDNODE

@NODE "3.06" "3.06"

 3.06 6-Feb-95    Internal Birthday version just to ßeta-Testers/Close Friends.
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° Some typos in docs removed. (And probably, some more
                  introduced! ;-)
                ° Removal of Sprite Garbage bug. Perhaps ;-Ţ
                  Doesn't seem to appear anymore.
                ° Removed a bug which caused random crashes since v3.02
                  I Was taking stuff off the stack in reverse order to what
                  I was shoving them on in the Initialisation routine!
                  Anything which relied upon a2/d2 after setting the
                  busypointer crashed!
                ° Changed interrupt priority from 136 to 10 !
                  The pointer now seems to animate at a slighty faster
                  speed than before, but still uses the same amount of
                  CPU-Time ;-)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "3.07" "3.07"

 3.07 29-Mar-95   ßeta-test release.
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° Supports Hires sprites (Sometimes) ;-Ţ
                  This version as far as I know, wasn't released, but I
                  may have inadvertantly sent it to a few people. (oops! ;-)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "4.0" "4.0"

 4.00 15-April-95 Fourth public release. PointerX is now Giftware!
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° Changed interrupt priority from 10 to -1
                  (Uses less CPU time - Hurrah! - Virtually nil when not in use)
                ° Added HiRes Support. Ta-da!
                  To All who requested it: Sorry it took so long, I got
                  a little lazy, and almost abandoned this project (Argh!)
                ° User can now select Sprite resolution via a shell Arg
                ° Now uses Spaces instead of Tabs in the doc/guide to
                  prevent looking ugly on non topaz font based Amiga's.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "4.01" "4.01"

 4.01 28-Aug-95   Fifth public release. (Quite a lot of work this time!)
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° Docs Spell Checking. (Again ;-)
                ° Guide file now works (Sorry! Don't know what happened
                  in v4.0! Guess I forgot to test it before release?)
                ° Misc code re-arranging. (Improved logic)
                ° As usual, a few optimisations!
                ° Added constant recognition string for VirusKillers
                ° Changed of busy-detection from word arithmetic to long.
                  (Should stop some instances of PtrX activating when it
                   shouldn't.)
                ° Patches are now made between a Forbid()/Permit() pair.
                ° Added SINGLEHAND option.
                ° Some programmers call SetPointer() with a zero for
                  the address of PointerData in order to blank the pointer
                  (For picture viewers e.t.c.) This was causing a few
                   problems since ..? Now Fixed)
                ° Added recognition for some other busy-pointers.
                  > Resource's SandGlass
                  > Model 4D's Zzz Cloud
                  > GBRoute's Watch
                  > Personal Paint 4's No-Entry Sign
                  > DPaint 3's 1.3 Cloud
                  > Sound FX's 1.3 Cloud
                    *NB - Note, that these cloud busy-ptrs may be used
                     in other software too, and will therefore be
                     automatically recognised.
                ° Completely re-wrote Seg-Split routines. Improvements:
                  - No longer crashes Mungwall on removal
                  - Now works from WorkBench or SHELL (How come no-one
                    reported that it never worked from WorkBench before?)
                  - Can now (For eg) be started from shell, and then quit
                    by running from WorkBench (Or vice-versa)
                  - Slightly more structured than the previous incarnation.
                ° Older versions allocated too more chipram for the sprite
                  than what was actually needed. (144 Bytes) Now, I alloc
                  the correct amount (just a miniscule 68 Bytes)
                ° There is an Exec/CopyMem() call in the startup which dates
                  back to Steve Tibbett days. I assumed it was the correct
                  value, and so carried on. I now discover that it was
                  copying 64 bytes of busypointer data instead of 16.
                  So now PointerX init's a few CPU cycles faster!
                ° Now reads Window/WD_Screen instead of GfxBase/ActiveView.
                  Should be friendlier to the OS.
                ° Now sets Sprite-Resolution prior to setting SpriteData.
                  No more brief flickers of the Lo-res pointer when in
                  Hi-res mode.
                ° No longer any chance of crashing while IPrefs changes the
                  screenmode e.t.c., Also removed a possible Enforcer hit.
                ° Uses approx 4k less memory! Now uses a 200 byte stack instead
                  of a 4K one, plus some startup code has now been moved, so it
                  no longers stays in memory.
                ° Some people suggested I change the interrupt priority to 0
                  so I did. Hope it makes you feel better ?!
                ° Added Super hires switch for DBLPAL users.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "4.01b" "4.01b"

 4.01b 06-Sep-95  Bug fix release
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° Fixed a bug, which meant that 4.01 crashed when run from
                  WorkBench.
                ° Removed a mungwall crash when quitting PointerX.
                ° Spelt a name wrong in the thanks (Sorry Ronny! ;^)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "4.02" "4.02"

 4.02 17-Nov-95   This time, I removed more code than I added!
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° Done away with the task which sits around waiting
                  for a Ctrl-C signal. Now you have to reload PtrX
                  to remove it from memory.
                ° Moved everything into one hunk, cut down executable size.
                ° Better memory allocation.
                  Uses less than 2k overall mem usage!
                ° 120 Bytes shorter than v4.01b!
                ° Improved Sprite-mem alignment.
                ° Change Pointer HotSpot to centre of sprite.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "4.03" "4.03"

 4.03 26-Nov-95
                ° Added some Workbench tooltype reading code.
                  currently supports SPRITERES and SINGLEHAND tooltypes.
                ° One or two small optimisations.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "4.04" "4.04"

 4.04 3-Dec-95    Bug Fix Release
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° Reorg was displaying a busy-pointer when it wasn't busy.
                  I Added some code which ignores the `Delayed-busypointer'
                  tag, and it now seemed to work. It doesn't work as it should,
                  (It should wait a while, then display a busy pointer, but
                   maybe that's for later!) I'm a little too busy right now,
                  so this is an intermediate bug-fix release.
                ° Removed the .doc from the distribution
                  I decided it was a waste of space.
                ° Added `commented-out' tooltypes to the Icon.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "4.05" "4.05"

 4.05 9-Mar-96    It's back!
                  ~~~~~~~~~~
                ° Improved instruction pipelining for 68020+
                ° No longer has the full $VER: string in the interrupt
                  name (I forgot to null terminate !)
                ° Changed the graphic data slightly, now the clock is
                  completely symettrical. [To my eyes anyhow!]
                ° Added some more icons! Thanks to Graham Maddox.
                ° File size shrunk a little due to hunk manipulation.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "4.06" "4.06"

 4.06 13-Mar-96   Slight optimisation.
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° Changed interrupt code so that it only redraws a frame of
                  animation if the busy pointer is currently visible.
                  This was wasting loads of CPU time previously.
                  Wish I'd only thought of it earlier.

                  I'm unsure if I actually sent this to anyone! Oops!
                  if not, I guess you'll never ever see it!
                  Consider it a Pointer-X `Rarity' ! ;^)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "4.07" "4.07"

 4.07 19-Mar-96   Fixes, Optimisations e.t.c....
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° Each time the hands were drawn, they were both read from
                  tables, inverted, and anded together.
                  I've now setup the tables as inverted data, so I don't
                  need to invert them in real-time. This also meant that I
                  had a spare scratch register free in my interrupt code,
                  and no longer had to push & pull d2 ! ;^)
                  What this means to you, the end user, is that your PtrX
                  executable is shorter, and yup, you guessed it..
                  a few nano-seconds FASTER!! (Only when actually busy)

                ° No longer has the full $VER: string in the interrupt
                  name (I forgot to null terminate !) Again! @{"(See v4.05)" Link "4.05"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "4.08" "4.08"

 4.08 14-Apr-96   Released at the `World Of Amiga show'.
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° One or two sneaky tricks to speed things up a little.
                ° Removed an enforcer hit that sneaked in in @{"v4.06" Link "4.06"}
                ° Removed a problem when removing PointerX, it reused some
                  memory after freeing it, which sometimes caused a crash.

                For the second time, PointerX made it onto the Amiga Shopper
                Subscribers disk, which Future Publishing kindly sent me a
                copy of. - Thanks!
@ENDNODE

@NODE "4.09" "4.09"

 4.09 30-Apr-96   Speeeed!
                  ~~~~~~~~
                ° Even more sneaky tricks to use as little CPU time as
                  possible. (Especially the interrupt code)
                ° Removed some redundant code
                ° Restructured some spaghetti code... yeuch!
                ° Removed a bug, SINGLEHAND made both hands disappear!
                  This was introduced during @{"v4.07!" Link "4.07"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "4.10" "4.10"

 4.10 13-May-96   More Speeeed!
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° Aligned interrupt code, and both patches to 32bit boundaries
                  which will decrease CPU usage on 68020+ machines ;^)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "4.11" "4.11"

 4.11 22-May-96   Bugs`n'speed!
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° Changed Memory allocations:
                    - Now sets Memf_Reverse to minimise memory fragmentation
                    - Also sets Memf_Public, so that my code doesn't get
                      swapped out to virtual memory! (Was potentially dangerous)
                ° Sprite is now aligned to 32bit boundary for enhanced video
                   throughput on AGA machines
                ° Removed PGP support, as no-one requested my keyfile, I guess
                   not everyone is as paranoid as me ;^)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "4.12" "4.12"

 4.12 29-May-96   Another new option (Oooh!)
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° Added an option NORESETHANDS (ToolType and shell arg)
                  which prevents PointerX from reseting to 12:00 every time
                  it's active.
                  Quite a few users requested this, and it was only a few
                  lines of code, so I thought.. what the hell ;^)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "4.13" "4.13"

 4.13 18-Jun-96   Zzz.. Bug fix..
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° If someone called OpenWindowTaglist() with the WA_Busypointer
                  tag in the taglist, the pointer wouldn't animate.
                  I now patch OpenWindowTaglist() to fix this.
                ° Slight optimisation in the SetPointer() patch.
                ° Moved the hot-spot of the busy pointer.
                ° Rewrote the sprite resolution changing code.
                  Should kill some reports, that the res code didn't work 100%
                  on every set-up.
                ° Removed the anger section of the docs, as someone took
                  offence to what I had written, which is not what I intended.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "4.14" "4.14"

 4.14             Not released.
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° Small optimisations in the interrupt code.
                ° SetBusyPointer was using Longs, now uses Words, as the
                  upper 16 bits are ignored anyhow.
                ° Rewrote the registration form. Not that it gets used much.
                  HINT HINT... Thanks to Maxine Gamboni for pointing out the
                  spelling mistakes. Also, apologies to Timo Rossi, as I sort
                  of stole the form from the FileMaster distribution, and
                  altered it a little, and ahem.. kept his mistakes intact ;^)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "4.15" "4.15"

 4.15 28-Sep-96   Darn then bugs...
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° Removed a possible bug in the library open code.
                ° Replaced the resolution changing code, that somehow got
                  removed.
                ° Small optimisations.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "4.16" "4.16"

 4.16 02-Oct-96   The stupid mistakes are always the last to be found.
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° Since time began, there has been a bug in PointerX, which
                  rears it's ugly head once every 10,000,000 runs.
                  Today I got it appearing several times in a row, after
                  writing myself a simple test tool.
                  And now at last I found out why. I wasn't telling the system
                  about the patches I had applied, so the next time the lib was
                  checksummed, a guru would appear. Six lines of code added,
                  to checksum the intuition.library when installing/removing
                  the patch were all it took, to nail this bug DEAD! FOREVER!
                  May it's bits Rest in Pieces.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "4.17" "4.17"

 4.17 26-Mar-97   The final release (By me)
                  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                ° Removed the checksumming introduced in v4.16, as it
                  was wholely unnecessary.
                ° Changed assembled to PhxAss, which made some extra
                  optimisations.
@ENDNODE
